{
  "text": "In a series of reviews of aquatic toxicity testing, McCarty et al. [CITATION_1] pointed out that regulatory demands have increased, while the quality of many data in well-accepted databases is often inadequate. This is because, in the translation from conceptual models to operational testing models, not all important toxicity modifying factors influencing linkages between fundamental thermodynamics and kinetic processes and adverse toxic effects associated with conventional dose metrics are considered.",
